6 theory becomes reality, hopefully the i915<br />people will also have figured out how to do the cache flushing<br />properly.<br /><br />And hopefully that "do it properly" ends up being simply that the<br />particular configuration that ends up being portable simply doesn't<br />need to do it at all and can statically just not build it,<br />sidestepping the issue entirely.<br /><br />Fingers crossed.<br /><br />.. of course, I'm also sure some clueless hardware engineer is still<br />convinced that non-coherent IO is the way to go for graphics, and that<br />doing cross-CPU IPIs to write back all caches is somehow still a valid<br />model. Because some people were still convinced about that not _that_<br />long ago. Hopefully reality (perhaps in the form of Apple) has caused<br />people to finally reconsider.<br /><br />                 Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
